main event: A witness observed a bright white object with an orange tail over Evanston, Illinois on December 7, 1965.
interesting points: The object moved westward at a high speed, closing in on an aircraft landing light.
The object was in sight for 3 minutes before disappearing behind trees.
The sky was hazy, making it difficult to see details clearly.
The witness had poor night vision and astigmatism, which may have affected their observation.
The witness had previously written to Dr. Hynek, an astronomer involved with Project Blue Book, but was disappointed with the results.
sighted object: A bright white object with an orange tail
